{{for|the fictional character|Charlotte Adams (Home and Away)}}
'''Charlotte A. Adams''' (later '''Charlotte A. Cunningham''') (born 1859) was an [[Australia]]n [[mountain climber]]. She became the first woman of [[European ethnic groups|European]] descent to climb to the peak of [[Mount Kosciuszko]] in February 1881, aged 21.<ref name="ciau.com.au">{{cite web |url=http://www.ciau.com.au/snow/charlottepass/ |title= Overview - Charlotte Pass ski resort |work= Cyber Interchange Australia |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080515220224/http://www.ciau.com.au/snow/charlottepass/|archivedate=15 May 2008}}</ref>

==Biography==
In February 1881, Adams accompanied her father, [[Philip Francis Adams]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article122107787|title=A marvellous time to visit the Main Range|first=John|last=Turnbull|date=15 October 1987|page=18|newspaper=The Canberra Times}}</ref> on a [[surveying]] trip to the Cooma district. On the trip, she climbed to the Peak of [[Mount Kosciuszko]], becoming the first known [[European ethnic groups|European]] woman to have made the climb.<ref name="ciau.com.au"/>

Adams married Herbert Norfolk Cunningham on 19 April 1882.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article28380266|title=Family Notices|newspaper=The Sydney Morning Herald|date=5 May 1882|page=8|quote=CUNNINGHAM-ADAMS—April 19, North Shore, by Rev. S. H. Childs, Herbert Norfolk Cunningham to Charlotte A. Adams.}}</ref>

==Legacy==
[[File:Charlotte´s Pass - village - panoramio.jpg|thumb|Charlotte Pass village is named for Charlotte Adams]]
The village of [[Charlotte Pass, New South Wales]] is named after Adams.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.canberratimes.com.au/act-news/tim-the-yowie-man-the-mouat-tree-project-is-a-great-cause-for-canberra-20150622-ghuifm.html|title=Tim the Yowie Man: The Mouat Tree Project is a great cause for Canberra|author=Tim the Yowie Man|author-link=Tim the Yowie Man|date=26 June 2015|newspaper=The Canberra Times|publisher=Fairfax Media|archiveurl=http://www.canberratimes.com.au/act-news/tim-the-yowie-man-the-mouat-tree-project-is-a-great-cause-for-canberra-20150622-ghuifm.html|archivedate=26 August 2015}}</ref>

