'''Keith Edward Barber''' (1944<ref>{{cite web |title=ISNI 0000000115965137 Barber, K. E. (1944-) |url=http://www.isni.org/isni/0000000115965137 |publisher=[[ISNI]] |accessdate=18 June 2018}}</ref> – 1 February 2017)<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.southampton.ac.uk/blog/sussed-news/2017/02/09/obituary-for-professor-keith-barber/ |title=Obituary for Professor Keith Barber |publisher=University of Southampton |date=2017-02-09 |access-date=2017-03-13 }}</ref><ref>https://www.thegazette.co.uk/notice/2721481</ref> was a [[professor]] of [[physical geography]] at the [[University of Southampton]]. Barber specialized in [[palaeoecology]], landscape and [[climate]] change, and human impact throughout the [[Quaternary]]. He retired in 2009.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.southampton.ac.uk/geography/news/2014/10/23_professor_keith_barber_profile.page |title=Professor Keith Barber – Pioneer of research on climate change and inspiring the next generation of scientists |publisher=University of Southampton |date=2014-10-23 |access-date=2017-03-13 }}</ref>
